Solve the lab by accessing the admin panel and deleting the user "carlos".

## Root Cause
The application identified administrators using a user-controlled and forgeable cookie value instead of enforcing proper server-side authorization checks.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application
2. Log in with normal user credentials
3. Intercept the request using Burp Suite
4. Identify the forgeable admin cookie parameter
5. Modify the cookie value to `true`
6. Reload the page
7. Access the admin panel
8. Delete the user "carlos"

## Impact
An attacker can manipulate the request parameter to gain unauthorized administrative access and perform privileged actions.

## Prevention
- Enforce server-side authorization checks
- Avoid trusting client-controlled parameters
- Validate user roles securely on the server
- Use secure session management

## What I Learned
This lab helped me understand how trusting client-controlled parameters can lead to privilege escalation and unauthorized administrative access.
